1:49 PM Defendant Catherine M. Young not in court.  Attorney Laura Kohl in court for State of Wisconsin. States witness present. Based on the defendants non appearance the State requests a warrant to issue. Court orders warrant to issue. Body Only Continental US. 2:03 PM Defendant arrives in Court. The Court orders the warrant to not issue. Defendant does not have Attorney present. Defendant states she does qualify for SPD. The judicial assistant calls the SPD office. The SPD did not receive all of the information they requested. The Court proceeds with the preliminary hearing. Daniel Skatrud sworn on oath & testifies. Witness identifies the defendant. Defendant does not question the witness and the witness is excused from the witness stand. Defendant does not testify. Court finds probable cause.  Defendant bound over for trial. Attorney Kohl gives the court paper copy of information, clerk scans in information. Matter to be set over for arraignment. Information filed.  Court advises defendant of charges & penalties. Bond continues.
Arraignment scheduled for October 19, 2022 at 03:30 pm.
